> The 3.75 oz rum pour is the historical Papa Doble (Daiquiri No. 4) double-size that Hemingway actually drank — accurate to the El Floridita house spec but a stunt drink by modern standards. The contemporary craft guest spec (Death & Co lineage) is 2 oz rum / 0.75 oz lime / 0.5 oz grapefruit / 0.25 oz Luxardo Maraschino / 0.25 oz simple, shaken and strained; the 6 drops of maraschino here read as roughly 0.25 oz Luxardo in modern measure.
>
> Brand recommendations. Best: Havana Club 3 Año (where legal) or Banks 5 Island for the white Cuban-style rum, Luxardo Maraschino (canonical for Floridita). Economical: Plantation 3 Stars or Bacardi Heritage for the rum, Luxardo Maraschino (still the value pick — Maraska is acceptable but markedly less elegant).

In a #blender{} combine @fresh lime juice{1%oz}, @fresh grapefruit juice{1%oz}, @maraschino liqueur{6%drops}, @white Cuban rum{3.75%oz}, and @crushed ice{1%cup}.
Blend on high for ~{5%seconds} until slushy.
Pour unstrained into a chilled #double coupe{}.
Garnish with a @lime wheel{1}.
